{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:second-esdras.11",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Esdras 11 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:1",
      "text": "It came to pass the second night that I saw a dream, and behold, an eagle which had twelve feathered wings and three heads came up from the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:2",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, she spread her wings over all the earth, and all the winds of heaven blew on her, and the clouds were gathered together against her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:3",
      "text": "I saw, and out of her wings there grew other wings near them; and they became little, tiny wings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:4",
      "text": "But her heads were at rest. The head in the middle was larger than the other heads, yet rested it with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:5",
      "text": "Moreover I saw, and behold, the eagle flew with her wings to reign over the earth and over those who dwell therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:6",
      "text": "I saw how all things under heaven were subject to her, and no one spoke against her—no, not one creature on earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:7",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, the eagle rose on her talons, and uttered her voice to her wings, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:8",
      "text": "“Don’t all watch at the same time. Let each one sleep in his own place and watch in turn;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:9",
      "text": "but let the heads be preserved for the last.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:10",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, the voice didn’t come out of her heads, but from the midst of her body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:11",
      "text": "I counted her wings that were near the others, and behold, there were eight of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:12",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, on the right side one wing arose and reigned over all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:13",
      "text": "When it reigned, the end of it came, and it disappeared, so that its place appeared no more. The next wing rose up and reigned, and it ruled a long time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:14",
      "text": "It happened that when it reigned, its end came also, so that it disappeared, like the first.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:15",
      "text": "Behold, a voice came to it, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:16",
      "text": "“Listen, you who have ruled over the earth all this time! I proclaim this to you, before you disappear,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:17",
      "text": "none after you will rule as long as you, not even half as long.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:18",
      "text": "Then the third arose, and ruled as the others before, and it also disappeared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:19",
      "text": "So it went with all the wings one after another, as every one ruled, and then disappeared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:20",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, in process of time the wings that followed were set up on the right side, that they might rule also. Some of them ruled, but in a while they disappeared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:21",
      "text": "Some of them also were set up, but didn’t rule.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:22",
      "text": "After this I saw, and behold, the twelve wings disappeared, along with two of the little wings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:23",
      "text": "There was no more left on the eagle’s body, except the three heads that rested, and six little wings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:24",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, two little wings divided themselves from the six and remained under the head that was on the right side; but four remained in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:25",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, these under wings planned to set themselves up and to rule.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:26",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, there was one set up, but in a while it disappeared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:27",
      "text": "A second also did so, and it disappeared faster than the first.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:28",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, the two that remained also planned between themselves to reign.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:29",
      "text": "While they thought about it, behold, one of the heads at rest awakened, the one that was in the middle, for that was greater than the two other heads.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:30",
      "text": "I saw how it joined the two other heads with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:31",
      "text": "Behold, the head turned with those who were with it, and ate the two under wings that planned to reign.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:32",
      "text": "But this head held the whole earth in possession, and ruled over those who dwell in it with much oppression. It had stronger governance over the world than all the wings that had gone before.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:33",
      "text": "After this I saw, and behold, the head also that was in the middle suddenly disappeared, like the wings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:34",
      "text": "But the two heads remained, which also reigned the same way over the earth and over those who dwell in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:35",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, the head on the right side devoured the one that was on the left side.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:36",
      "text": "Then I heard a voice, which said to me, “Look in front of you, and consider the thing that you see.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:37",
      "text": "I saw, and behold, something like a lion roused out of the woods roaring. I heard how he sent out a man’s voice to the eagle, and spoke, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:38",
      "text": "“Listen and I will talk with you. The Most High will say to you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:39",
      "text": "‘Aren’t you the one that remains of the four animals whom I made to reign in my world, that the end of my times might come through them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:40",
      "text": "The fourth came and overcame all the animals that were past, and ruled the world with great trembling, and the whole extent of the earth with grievous oppression. He lived on the earth such a long time with deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:41",
      "text": "You have judged the earth, but not with truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:42",
      "text": "For you have afflicted the meek, you have hurt the peaceful, you have hated those who speak truth, you have loved liars, destroyed the dwellings of those who produced fruit, and threw down the walls of those who did you no harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:43",
      "text": "Your insolence has come up to the Most High, and your pride to the Mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:44",
      "text": "The Most High also has looked at his times, and behold, they are ended, and his ages are fulfilled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:45",
      "text": "Therefore appear no more, you eagle, nor your horrible wings, nor your evil little wings, nor your cruel heads, nor your hurtful talons, nor all your worthless body,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-esdras.11.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-esdras",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Esdras 11:46",
      "text": "that all the earth may be refreshed and relieved, being delivered from your violence, and that she may hope for the judgment and mercy of him who made her.’”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
